1 unit Baby Lettuce
1 unit Tomato
2 unit Demi-Baguette
2 tablespoon Mayonnaise
1.5 ounce Italian Dressing
¼ cup Monterey Jack Cheese
8 ounce Smoked Deli Ham

• Wash and dry produce.

• Trim and discard root end from lettuce; halve lettuce lengthwise
(don't separate into leaves!). Finely slice half the lettuce crosswise; cut
remaining lettuce into two wedges (four wedges for 4 servings). Thinly
slice tomato into rounds.

• Halve and toast baguettes.

• Meanwhile, in a small bowl, combine mayonnaise and dressing.

• Fill toasted baguettes with Monterey Jack, ham, sliced lettuce, tomato
rounds, and half the creamy dressing.

• Halve subs on a diagonal.

• Divide subs and lettuce wedges between plates. Drizzle wedges with
remaining creamy dressing and serve.